RACE.RACE_TEXT: DEL MAR RACE 1 1M Turf CR: 98. Claiming Purse 53000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races At A Mile Or Over Since May 31 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since Then Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $40,000, if for $35,000, allowed 2 lbs. (Maiden Races And Claiming Races For $32,000 Or Less Not Considered). (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: POST FACTO pulled early vying three deep into the first turn then chased outside the top pair into the backstretch, tugged forward to challenge again in the middle stages, dueled into and around the far turn and put a head in front at the quarter pole, vied between rivals into the lane, lost command to SILENT SUNDAY in upper stretch but fought back gamely from inside and dug in to edge outer rivals. TOM AND JAZZY pulled from inside early, continued to chase from the rail under a hold in the middle stages, moved to the two path on the far turn, came out and bumped rival entering the stretch, rallied outside the top pair and missed. SILENT SUNDAY stalked in the two path between rivals early, bid three deep on the far turn, fought three wide into the lane, took over in upper stretch, dueled with POST FACTO in the final furlong and was outfinished between rivals late. HACKING IT UP stalked three deep around both turns, got floated out entering the stretch and finished willingly for a minor award. ACQUIRED CLASS vied inside a pair of rivals into the first turn then ceded command, stalked up the backstretch, coaxed around the far turn, lacked room past the quarter pole and raced in traffic to midstretch before tipping to a clear path but was too late to unleash a rally. EDDIE'S LAST vied between foes into the first turn, cleared inner rival early on the backstretch but was soon pressured by POST FACTO, dueled with that rival into and around the far turn, lost command at the quarter pole, weakened in the furlong grounds and was not persevered with late. THEMAINPROTAGONIST (IRE) was off slow to begin, had the rider take a big hold crossing the finish line for the first time, trailed along the inside through both turns, altered out to avoid fallen rider at the top of the stretch and never got involved. UPWARD MOBILITY traveled outside a rival near the back early, traveled two to three wide on the far turn, took up at the three-sixteenths and clipped fallen rider, was eased through the lane and walked off. SINGLE TRACK MIND (IRE) tucked inside on the clubhouse turn, moved into striking range between rivals in the middle stages, waited for room on the far turn behind the leaders, got bumped from inside and clipped heels entering the stretch, losing his rider in the process, was eventually caught following the race and walked off. FOLLOWING AN INQUIRY, THE STEWARDS DISQUALIFIED TOM AND JAZZY FROM SECOND AND PLACED HIM UNPLACED FOR SHIFTING OUT AND CAUSING SINGLE TRACK MIND (IRE) TO CLIP HEELS AND UNSEAT HIS RIDER ENTERING THE STRETCH.

YOU'REINTHEARMYNOW chased along the inside, tipped out leaving the bend and lacked further response. RACE.FOOTNOTES: LUKA GRAZIE stalked from inside, went up inside troubled trio to take over on the clubhouse turn, set the pace to the far turn, drew away around the bend, padded the lead in upper stretch, shorted a bit late but was able to hold on. GET THE GOLD unhurried in the beginning, was on the move through the far turn but ran into traffic from the five-sixteenths to the quarter pole, moved out into the clear, closed fast and in the furlong grounds but ran out of time. DARK MARCUS was a bit rank on the inside first time through the stretch, moved closer outside a rival in the middle stages, rounded the far turn two then three wide and finished evenly for the show. MAXVILLE trailed on the inside, altered out at the five-eighths pole, gained outside a rival then angled five wide at the quarter pole, leveled off the in the lane but still earned a minor award. SILENT HEAT pressed from between then outside the leader early, got bumped and forced out around the clubhouse turn, remained close outside the new leader up the backstretch, chased that rival two wide around the far turn and weakened down the lane. BIG GEORGE coaxed outside a rival off the pace first time through the stretch, tucked inside on the clubhouse turn, dropped back exiting the backstretch, cut the corner into the lane, moved out in the lane and improved. AVIATOR NATION tracked along the inside, ridden along into the far turn, looked to advance up the fence but was in a bit tight around that bend and weakened down the lane. SILVER N BLACK attended the pace three deep early, got forced wide around the first turn then came back into the three path leaving the bend, started to weaken around the far turn and tired in the lane. STOP WHINING vied for the lead inside a pair of rivals then started to pull and was rank first time through the stretch, lugged out and bumped SILENT HEAT then took up on the clubhouse turn, taken back to last, coaxed leaving the backstretch, trailed into the lane, eased down the stretch and walked off.

LIBERAL LADY took control early in the two path entering the first turn then moved inside, given her cue when under heavy pressure around the far turn, lost the lead in upper stretch but fought back and battled between rivals through the furlong grounds and finished a game second. CLIQUISH stalked along the rail then had to pause when racing on the heels of the leader into the backstretch, remained along the inside through the far turn and into the stretch, launched a bid inside the top pair with a furlong left to run, battled to the wire and proved a game third. ROSE DAWSON stalked two wide then had to alter out from behind TROUVILLE on the clubhouse turn, chased in the three path through the far turn and failed to produce a bid. ACT OF SERENDIPITY tracked three then four deep early, remained wide through the far turn, was under a drive five wide into the lane and lacked a rally. UNFAITHFUL WAYS brushed the gate to lose a step at the start, trailed two wide early, rounded the far turn two then three wide and failed to respond when called upon.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: ANACARO dueled for the lead from outside, vied three deep into and around the far turn, fought through the lane, carried a short lead into the final sixteenth and dug in to prevail. ENCLOSURE settled inside then moved a bit off the rail on the clubhouse turn, angled out and moved into range in the middle stages, asked four deep on the far turn, drew alongside ANACARO in midstretch, fought to the wire but could not get by. COLETTE'S JOY settled in the three path, drew closer leaving the backstretch, navigated the far turn two then tipped three wide leaving the bend, hemmed in by outer rival at the top of the stretch, lacked room behind ANACARO through the stretch and would not be let out by ENCLOSURE, moved in late and got up for the show. CONQUISTAR chased along the inside while keen running up on the heels of the leader on the first turn, went between the top pair at the half-mile pole to challenge, vied between rivals around the far turn while holding a slim advantage at the quarter pole, lost the lead entering the lane, fought back down the stretch and was outfinished in the late stages. CON SEAL AND KERRY rated between then outside a rival on the first turn, traveled three deep leaving the backstretch, weakened under coaxing on the far turn, spun three wide into the lane and flattened. IRISH MYTH stumbled leaving the gate, chased four wide early, moved out further up the backstretch, went five then four wide around the second bend and came up empty. DUCHESSOFBAYRIDGE stumbled ever so slightly at the start while still breaking best, moved over to the inside then dueled with ANACARO, vied with outer rivals past the half-mile pole, fought through the far turn along the rail, weakened in upper stretch and faded. GOLDEN SKYLINE broke a few lengths slow from outside, trailed five wide into the clubhouse turn, angled in for the last bend and never got involved.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DEL MAR RACE 8 1M Dirt CR: 74. Maiden Claiming Purse 30000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MIMSY tracked four wide early, bid four deep at the midway point, fought outside rivals through the far turn, led five wide into the lane, kicked clear upper stretch and drew off. VULIN coaxed from the gate, pressed from outside then vied between foes past the half-mile pole, battled through the far turn and into the stretch, could not keep pace with MIMSY outside the eight pole, churned on through the final furlong and regained second from PRINCESS TENKO late. PRINCESS TENKO chased three deep around the first turn, engaged the top pair at the half-mile pole, fought three deep between foes around the far turn, lost touch with the winner approaching the final furlong and got outfinished by VULIN for the place honors. FAST INVESTMENT broke out and bumped twice at the start, went up to take control and led two wide around the clubhouse turn, set the pace under pressure then vied inside trio of rivals up the backstretch, lost command but fought back through the far turn, could not keep pace with outer rivals exiting that bend and flattened to fourth. MIDNIGHT SILENCE bumped with FAST INVESTMENT then got sandwiched between rivals and clipped heels at the start, reserved in the two path early, moved out three deep in the middle stages, asked around the far turn, went three to four wide wide leaving that bend and could not rally. BOGINSKAYA broke in, bumped then lost her path in the beginning, chased five wide through both turns and also lacked a rally. BILLY GALLIVAN bumped with outer rival then shifted inward to bump another foe, tugged the rider along in the two path early, dropped back under coaxing on the far turn and had little left for the drive. DOOZY was keen early when asked to rate on the inside, pushed around the far turn but began to weaken and faded out of contention. TAPIT ROCKS broke slow, climbed at the back early off the rail, remained off the rail to the far turn, spun four wide into the lane and was not a factor. SHAMBALA GIRL took back early and moved inside, ridden along into the far turn, trailed a bit off the rail into the stretch and could not make an impact.
